Yes @olitomlinson, thanks for the reply.

@yaron2, @atrauzzi and @JoshVanL have some context.

I think the crux of the issue is that we've found ourselves in some edge-case scenarios, and at times have had to roll back, so our usage of dapr sometimes does not follow the happy path; having a tool like this would be helpful going forward for just understanding and analyzing the state storage.
